title: Slow Cooker Ramen Soup
summary: Slow Cooker Ramen Soup might be just the main course you are searching for. One serving contains 699 calories, 52g of protein, and 26g of fat. For $4.44 per serving, this recipe covers 45% of your daily requirements of vitamins and minerals. A couple people made this recipe, and 12 would say it hit the spot. It is perfect for Autumn. It is a good option if you're following a dairy free diet. If you have scallions, radishes, ginger, and a few other ingredients on hand, you can make it. To use up the fresh ginger you could follow this main course with the Fresh Ginger Cookies as a dessert. All things considered, we decided this recipe deserves a spoonacular score of 87%. This score is excellent. Try Slow-Cooker Chicken and Ramen Noodle Soup, Slow Cooker Japanese Pork and Ramen Soup, and Slow Cooker Pork Ramen for similar recipes.

winePairing.pairingText: Ramen Noodles works really well with Riesling, Sake, and Sauvignon Blanc. Saké is an obvious choice when it comes to Japanese food. If you want to stick to grape wine, though, you might opt for sauvignon blanc or riesling. The Dr. Loosen Dr. L Riesling with a 4.6 out of 5 star rating seems like a good match. It costs about 11 dollars per bottle.

productMatches.title: Dr. Loosen Dr. L Riesling
productMatches.description: "...a surprisingly complex and outstanding value in nearly-dry Riesling... Lemon, green apple, wet stone, and lightly floral aromas are followed by a crisp, slate-saturated palate and a finish of juicy citrus and apple, nut oils, mineral salts, and wet stone..."-Wine Advocate"This wine has to be one of the best deals in Mosel Riesling. Ernst Loosen's 'introductory' Riesling is marked by flavors of fresh peach and apricot, balanced by a fair amount of refreshing acidity. A great aperitif."- Food & Wine Magazine

instructions: Place all the broth ingredients in a slow cooker and cook on low for 6-8 hours or high for 2-3.When you are ready to eat, skim any fat or floating scum that might be on the top of the broth from the meat. Remove the garlic, ginger pieces, and scallions (if desired).Remove the meat and slice or shred it, setting it aside with your other prepared toppings.Turn the crock pot to high and add your mushrooms (if using) and ramen noodles. Cook the noodles for the time directed on their packaging, and then check them. Since your broth probably isn't boiling, the noodles may take up to twice as long as the package directs to soften.Place a serving of noodles into a bowl and ladle the hot broth over the noodles.Top as desired and slurp away!

steps.step: Place all the broth ingredients in a slow cooker and cook on low for 6-8 hours or high for 2-3.When you are ready to eat, skim any fat or floating scum that might be on the top of the broth from the meat.
Remove the garlic, ginger pieces, and scallions (if desired).

Remove the meat and slice or shred it, setting it aside with your other prepared toppings.Turn the crock pot to high and add your mushrooms (if using) and ramen noodles. Cook the noodles for the time directed on their packaging, and then check them. Since your broth probably isn't boiling, the noodles may take up to twice as long as the package directs to soften.
Place a serving of noodles into a bowl and ladle the hot broth over the noodles.Top as desired and slurp away!
